==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''[[square leg]] [[umpire]]'''
#{{cricket}} The [[umpire]] who stands at or near [[square leg]] to rule on [[decision]]s at the [[batsman]]'s end of the [[wicket]]. In some circumstances, the umpire may stand at the equivalent position on the opposite side of the batsman (between [[gully]] and [[point]]), but is still referred to as the square leg umpire in these circumstances.